<h2>Detailed steps for the process of installing the software:</h2>
<ol>
    <li>
1. **Create a GitHub repository**
        <ul>
 <li>- Sign in to your GitHub account.   </li>
 <li>- Click on the '+' icon at the top right corner and select   'New repository'.   </li>
 <li>- Name your repository and provide a description.   </li>
 <li>- Choose whether the repository should be public or private.   </li>
 <li>- Initialize the repository with a README file, if necessary.   </li>
 <li>- Click on 'Create repository'.
        </ul>
    </li>
<li>2. **Create a strata to replace the old catalyst repository with the new one**
    <ul>
<li>- Clone the new repository to your local machine using the command `git clone  &lt;repository_url &lt;`.</li>
 <li>   - Navigate to the cloned repository's directory.
    <li>- Create a new branch for the strata using the command `git checkout -b  &lt;branch_name &lt;`.</li>
    <li>    - Make the necessary changes to replace the old catalyst repository.</li>
    <li>    - Stage the changes using the command `git add .`.</li>
    <li>    - Commit the changes using the command `git commit -m " &lt;commit_message &lt;"`.</li>
            <li> - Push the changes to the remote repository using the command `git push origin  &lt;branch_name &lt;`.</li>
                           </ul>
</li>
              <li>  3. **Update the repository on the production server**
                         <ul>
                <li>- SSH into the production server.</li>
               <li> - Navigate to the directory where the repository is located.</li>
                <li>- Pull the latest changes from the remote repository using the command `git pull origin master`.</li>
  </ul>  </li>
 <li>               4. **Update the database for the new version**
                            <ul>
                <li>- Backup the current database.</li>
               <li> - Run the necessary SQL scripts to update the database schema.
                <li>- Test the new version of the application with the updated database.</li>
               <li> - If everything works as expected, commit the database changes.</li>  </ul>
                                </li>
</ol>
               <p>Remember to always test each step in a safe environment before applying them to the production server.</p>
